As Engrossed: H2/12/25 SB142
1 (2) The division shall promulgate rules defining what
2 constitutes a special event that occurs during the school day.
3 (e) A policy adopted and implemented under this section shall not
4 prohibit a student from using a personal electronic device during the school
5 day if the use of the personal electronic device is: (1) Included in the
6 student's:
7 (A) Individualized education program developed under the
8 Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, 20 U.S.C. § 1400 et seq., as it
9 existed on January 1, 2025; or
10 (B) Plan developed under Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act
11 of 1973, 29 U.S.C. § 794, as it existed on January 1, 2025; or
12 (2) Required for a student who is enrolled in an endorsed
13 concurrent enrollment course at an institution of higher education in order
14 to utilize two-factor authentication to access course work and resources for
15 the endorsed concurrent enrollment course.
16 (f) Each public school district and open-enrollment public charter
17 school shall publish on its website its personal electronic device policy
18 required under this section before the first day of the school year each
19 year.
20 (g) A public school district or an open-enrollment public charter
21 school that fails to adopt or enforce the personal electronic device policy
22 required under this section, as determined by the division, shall be cited
23 for a violation of the Standards for Accreditation of Arkansas Public Schools
24 and School Districts.
25 (h) A public school district or an open-enrollment public charter
26 school shall not be liable for a personal electronic device that is
27 confiscated under the public school district's or open-enrollment public
28 charter school's personal electronic device policy required under this
29 section if the personal electronic device is lost, stolen, or damaged.
30 (i) The division shall promulgate rules necessary to implement this
31 section, including without limitation rules that:
32 (1) Govern the process for monitoring compliance with this
33 section; and
34 (2) Establish the process for approving or disapproving a policy
35 submitted to the division by a public school district or an open-enrollment
36 public charter school as required under subdivision (b)(2) of this section.
